Rating: 2
I made this recipe as written, except that I used a can of drained diced tomatoes. It seemed to me that the "sauce" was really more of a garlic-wine broth. I like the concept, but I would make it differently if I were to make again. I would not substitute canned tomatoes, and I would only use 1/2 cup (not 1 1/2 cups). I would skip the egg and cornstarch entirely. I would use more garlic, plus 1/4 tsp. crushed red pepper. I would only use 1/3 cup of wine. I might add mushrooms or lemon juice/zest. And the fresh basil is essential!

