Rating: 3
Two criticisms: I needed to know whether or not to drain the tomatoes, and when I drained the shrimp, should I run cold water over them so I don't get cooked egg whites in my sauce? Other than that, we enjoyed the dish. I will make it again, but with these modifications: I will make roasted garlic ahead of time (we couldn't really taste the garlic in this dish). I will NOT drain the tomatoes, I WILL run cold water over the shrimp before draining, and I will cook the shrimp separately in a pan of 2 tblspns olive oil and lots of roasted garlic for 3 minutes. Then, I'll put the shrimp on the pasta, and pour the sauce over it when it's cooked. Yum!

